d = NDeepDict(2, int)
assert len(d) == 0, 'Nothing is in new dict so length is 0'
assert len(d[['a']]) == 0, 'Nothing is in the second level dict so should be 0'
assert len(d
    ) == 1, "Looking for length of 'a' above should have added it to the first level dict, so now first level length is 0"
assert d['b'] == {}
assert 'b' in d
assert len(d[['b']]) == 0
d[['b', 'level2-a']
    ], 'Getting a key for first time in second level dict, so should create an item in b'
assert len(d[['b']]) == 1
assert d[['b', 'level2-a']] == 0
d[['b', 'level2-b']] += 50
assert d[['b', 'level2-b']] == 50
assert d.get(['b', 'level2-b']) == 50
